#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:63
msgid "Supported features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:66
msgid "SPI wiring modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:68
msgid "The driver currently supports the following SPI wiring configurations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:71
msgid "One lane mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:73
msgid ""
"In this mode, each channel has its own SDO line to send the conversion "
"results. At the moment this mode can only be used on AD4030 which has one "
"channel so only one SDO line is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:90
msgid "Interleaved mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:92
msgid ""
"In this mode, both channels conversion results are bit interleaved one SDO "
"line. As such the wiring is the same as `One lane mode`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:96
msgid "SPI offload wiring"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:116
msgid ""
"In this mode, both the ``cnv-gpios`` and a ``pwms`` properties are required. "
"The ``pwms`` property specifies the PWM that is connected to the ADC CNV "
"pin. The SPI offload will have a ``trigger-sources`` property to indicate "
"the SPI offload (PWM) trigger source. For AD4030 and similar ADCs, there are "
"two possible data transfer zones for sample N. One of them (zone 1) starts "
"after the data conversion for sample N is complete while the other one (zone "
"2) starts 9.8 nanoseconds after the rising edge of CNV for sample N + 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:124
msgid ""
"The configuration depicted in the above diagram is intended to perform data "
"transfer in zone 2. To achieve high sample rates while meeting ADC timing "
"requirements, an offset is added between the rising edges of PWM0 and PWM1 "
"to delay the SPI transfer until 9.8 nanoseconds after CNV rising edge. This "
"requires a specialized PWM controller that can provide such an offset. The "
"`AD4630-FMC HDL project`_, for example, can be configured to sample AD4030 "
"data during zone 2 data read window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:135
msgid "SPI Clock mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:137
msgid "Only the SPI clocking mode is supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:140
msgid "Output modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:142
msgid ""
"There are more exposed IIO channels than channels as describe in the devices "
"datasheet. This is due to the `Differential data + common-mode`_ encoding 2 "
"types of information in one conversion result. As such a \"device\" channel "
"provides 2 IIO channels, one for the differential data and one for the "
"common byte."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:149
msgid "Differential data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:151 ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:159
#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:170
msgid "This mode is selected when:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:153
msgid "Only differential channels are enabled in a buffered read"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:154 ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:162
msgid "Oversampling attribute is set to 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:157
msgid "Differential data + common-mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:161
msgid "Differential and common-mode channels are enabled in a buffered read"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:164
msgid ""
"For the 24-bits chips, this mode is also available with 16-bits differential "
"data but is not selectable yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:168
msgid "Averaged differential data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:172
msgid "Only differential channels are selected enabled in a buffered read"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:173
msgid "Oversampling attribute is greater than 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:176
msgid "Digital Gain and Offset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:178
msgid ""
"Each differential data channel has a 16-bits unsigned configurable hardware "
"gain applied to it. By default it's equal to 1. Note that applying gain can "
"cause numerical saturation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:182
msgid ""
"Each differential data channel has a signed configurable hardware offset. "
"For the ADCs ending in ``-24``, the gain is encoded on 24-bits. Likewise, "
"the ADCs ending in ``-16`` have a gain encoded on 16-bits. Note that "
"applying an offset can cause numerical saturation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:187
msgid ""
"The final differential data returned by the ADC is computed by first "
"applying the gain, then the offset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:190
msgid ""
"The gain is controlled by the ``calibscale`` IIO attribute while the offset "
"is controlled by the ``calibbias`` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:194
msgid "Reference voltage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:196
msgid ""
"The chip supports an external reference voltage via the ``REF`` input or an "
"internal buffered reference voltage via the ``REFIN`` input. The driver "
"looks at the device tree to determine which is being used. If ``ref-supply`` "
"is present, then the external reference voltage is used and the internal "
"buffer is disabled. If ``refin-supply`` is present, then the internal "
"buffered reference voltage is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:204
msgid "Reset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4030.rst:206
msgid ""
"Both hardware and software reset are supported. The driver looks first at "
"the device tree to see if the ``reset-gpio`` is populated. If not present, "
"the driver will fallback to a software reset by wiring to the device's "
"registers."
msgstr ""

